CRT Code Table:  TELTCALCRULEPERC1 = Client is still not 60 but is dead or retired (ALL conditions are fulfilled) => Preferential Tax Rate  TELTCALCRULEPERC2 = client is not retired and must pay the full tax (= Précompte professionnel)  TELTCALCRULEPERC3 = client has presented the form 276C1B, meaning that he has never declared his Pension Plan  TELTCALCRULEPERC4 = TELT at 60 years or 10 years later when opened after 55 years  TELTCALCRULEPERC5 = New anticipated tax of 1% (2015 – 2019)  TELTCALCRULEPERC6 = Star Fund account opened after 55 years, client is dead or retired (ALL conditions fulfilled)  TELTCALCRULEPERC7 = CRT code for the TUA 6,5 % (=UAT)  TELTCALCRULEPERC8 = Star Fund account opened after 55 years, client not dead or not retired  TELTCALCRULEPERC9 = Code used for Sell orders after TELT / PP has been paid. These sell orders are tax free.

Text.val: TELTCALCRULEPERC1 = Client is still not 60 but is dead or retired (ALL conditions are fulfilled) => Preferential Tax Rate
TELTCALCRULEPERC2 = Client is not retired and must pay the full tax (= Précompte professionnel)
TELTCALCRULEPERC3 = Client has presented the form 276C1B, meaning that he has never declared his Pension Plan
TELTCALCRULEPERC4 = TELT at 60 years or 10 years later when opened after 55 years
TELTCALCRULEPERC6 = Star Fund account opened after 55 years, client is dead or retired (ALL conditions fulfilled)
TELTCALCRULEPERC7 = CRT code for the TUA 6,5 % (=UAT)
TELTCALCRULEPERC8 = Star Fund account opened after 55 years, client not dead or not retired
TELTCALCRULEPERC9 = Code used for Sell orders after TELT / PP has been paid. These sell orders are tax free.
